THE CAPITAINE FAURE.* Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 20, 1925. No. 222. Davies, Auerbach & Cornell, of New York City (Chas. E. Hotchkiss and Alexander J. Feild, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Burlingham, Veeder, Masten & Fearey, of New York City (William J. Dean and Roseoe H. Hupper, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

Certiorari denied 45 S. Ct. 513, 69 L. Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

Decree (7 F.[2d] 131) affirmed with costs.
